inter2007/speakerlookslike.asp This Is What a Speaker Looks Like], the Winter 2007 cover story to ''[[Ms. magazine|Ms.]]''\n* [https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2020/03/25/how-nancy-pelosis-unlikely-rise-turned-her-into-most-powerful-woman-us-history/?arc404=true&utm_campaign=wp_week_in_ideas&utm_medium=email&utm_source=newsletter&wpisrc=nl_ideas ''A troublemaker with a gavel\", by Karen Tumulty, ''[[Washington Post]]'', March 25, 2020. Retrieved March 30, 2020.]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=Richard J. O'Neill}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[California Democratic Party|Chair of the California Democratic Party]]|years=1981\u20131983}}\n{{s-aft|after=Peter Kelly}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Gary Locke]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Response to the State of the Union address]]|years=[[2004 State of the Union Address|2004]], [[2005 State of the Union Address|2005]]|alongside=[[Tom Daschle]], [[Harry Reid]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Tim Kaine]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Bill Richardson]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of Democratic National Conventions|Permanent Chair of the Democratic National Convention]]|years=[[2008 Democratic National Convention|2008]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Antonio Villaraigosa]]}}\n|-\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Sala Burton]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from California|U.S. House of Representatives]]<br />from [[California's 5th congressional district]]|years=1987\u20131993}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Bob Matsui]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ron Dellums]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from California|U.S. House of Representatives]]<br />from [[California's 8th congressional district]]|years=1993\u20132013}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Paul Cook (politician)|Paul Cook]]}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Jackie Speier]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from California|U.S. House of Representatives]]<br />from [[California's 12th congressional district]]|years=2013\u2013present}}\n{{s-